                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13230965" author="ebourg" created="Fri, 16 Mar 2012 08:12:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good point but I&apos;m not sure it actually happens. So far the only application I have found supporting unicode escapes is HSQLDB. It can read them but doesn&apos;t write them (I checked HSQL 1.8, I&apos;ll look at 2.x). I believe these unicode escapes are typically created by a program like native2ascii which converts only non ascii characters, so I believe the line separators are safe.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I agree on removing the unicode escape setting from CSVFormat. I would prefer submitting the reader to &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;io&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; than making it public in &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;csv&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13231472" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Fri, 16 Mar 2012 18:14:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, I&apos;m working on removing it and moving the reader class to IO for a future release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
